This paper discusses the adverse effects of translationese on machine translation evaluation results, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the evaluation of machine translation systems, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques, making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The paper also provides a power analysis of tests used in machine translation evaluations, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the reliability of past evaluations, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, making cs.IR a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper provides a comprehensive check-list for future machine translation evaluation, which involves cybersecurity (cs.CY) techniques to ensure the security and privacy of the evaluation process.
